article.headline: Drexel 75, Hofstra 62
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Freshman Chris Fouch scored a career-high 29 points, hitting six 3-pointers, to lead Drexel to an easy 75-62 victory over Hofstra on Saturday. Fouch went 10-for-15 from the floor, scoring 19 points in the first half to give the Dragons (11-10, 6-3 Colonial Athletic Association) an 18-point lead at halftime. They pulled ahead by 30 points with 12:51 left in the second half. Gerald Colds finished with 15 points and Jamie Harris had 14 points and six assists for Drexel. Samme Givens had a game-high 11 rebounds -- four on the offensive glass. The Dragons shot 48.1 percent from the floor (26-for-54), while holding the Pride (9-12, 2-7) to 35.4 percent (23-for-65). Miklos Szabo led Hofstra with 14 points and Charles Jenkins scored 13 points.
